        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 1:30PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 130 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Vincent, or 10 miles southeast of Leeds. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Leeds, Moody, Vincent, Harpersville, Alpine Bay Resort, Bald Rock,
Vandiver, Coosa Island, Logan Martin Dam, Logan Martin Lake, Country
Club Estates, Sterrett, and Camp Winnataska.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
